meta.search_description: Overall summary of COVID-19 in circulation within the UK

title: COVID-19
page_description:
COVID-19 is a respiratory infection caused by the SARS-CoV-2 virus. Find out more about data collection for COVID-19.

The UKHSA data dashboard is still undergoing statistical review. For reporting and analytical purposes, use the COVID-19 dashboard and the weekly surveillance report.

value.title: Cases by specimen date
value.body: Number of cases by specimen date (the day the test was taken). Data for the last 5 days, highlighted in grey, is incomplete.

value.title: 7-day case rates by specimen date per 100,000 population
value.body: Rate of cases per 100,000 people in the rolling 7-day period ending on the date shown.

value.label: Rate of cases per 100,000 population in 7-day period

value.title: Case rates by age and sex per 100,000 population
value.body: Rates per 100,000 people of the total number of cases since the start of the COVID-19 pandemic, by age.

value.title: Daily deaths with COVID-19 on the death certificate by date of death.
value.body: Daily numbers of deaths of people whose death certificate mentioned COVID-19 as one of the causes, and 7-day rolling average. Because of the time it takes for deaths to be registered, there is a lag in reporting of at least 11 days. Data is not shown for the 14 days before the most recent reported date as it’s considered incomplete. Data is shown by date of death.

value.title: Patients admitted to hospital
value.body: Daily number of COVID-19 patients admitted to hospital.

value.title: Patients in hospital
value.body: Daily count of confirmed COVID-19 patients in hospital at 8am.

value.title: Hospital admissions rate per 100,000 population
value.body: Breakdown of people admitted to hospital with COVID-19, shown as the rate per 100,000 people, since the start of the pandemic.

value.title: Total daily number of PCR tests reported
value.body: The daily number of new PCR tests reported. Data is shown by specimen date (the date the sample was collected from the person).

value.title: Weekly positivity of people receiving a PCR test
value.body: The percentage of people who received a PCR test and had at least one positive COVID-19 PCR test result in the same 7 days. Data is shown by specimen date (the date the sample was collected).

value.title: People aged 75 and over who have had spring booster vaccinations, by vaccination date
value.body: The number of people aged 75 and over who have had a spring booster COVID-19 vaccination. Data for the latest 2 days, marked in grey, is incomplete. Data is shown by date of vaccination.

value.title: Spring booster vaccination uptake (75+), by vaccination date
value.body: The percentage of people aged 75 and over who have had a spring booster COVID-19 vaccination.

value.title: People aged 50 and over who have had autumn booster vaccinations, by vaccination date
value.body: The number of people aged 50 and over who have had an autumn booster COVID-19 vaccination. Data for the latest 2 days, marked in grey, is incomplete. Data is shown by date of vaccination.

value.title: Autumn booster vaccination uptake (50+), by vaccination date
value.body: The percentage of people aged 50 and over who have had an autumn booster COVID-19 vaccination.
